data.description:
- Multi-stage Dockerfile for a Next.js application using Node.js 22 Alpine
- Build stage:
  - Installs dependencies and builds the Next.js application
- Production stage:
  - Creates secure user/group for running the application
  - Copies only necessary files from build stage (built app, modules, public assets)
  - Exposes port 3000 for web traffic
  - Setup for production-ready Node.js application with minimal image size and security best practices
- Available to be used by container orchestration systems and deployment pipelines

- Main README file for Invoify, a web-based invoice generator application
- Key exports/information for other components:
  * Core technology stack: Next.js 13, TypeScript, React, Shadcn UI
  * Available features and functionality for integration
  * Required environment variables (NODEMAILER_EMAIL, NODEMAILER_PW)
  * Installation and setup instructions
  * Future roadmap features for planning
  * Compatibility notice regarding Firefox browser issues
  * License information (MIT)
The README serves as the primary documentation source for:
- Project overview and capabilities
- Technical requirements and dependencies
- Development setup process
- External integrations (email functionality)
- Current limitations and planned features

- A Next.js catch-all route handler (`[...rest]`) that handles any undefined routes
- Immediately triggers Next.js' built-in 404 Not Found page using `notFound()`
- Used for internationalization routes (`[locale]`) that don't match any defined paths
- Exports a default page component that other files don't need to import/use
- Serves as a fallback route handler for the application's routing system

- Root layout component for a Next.js application with internationalization support
- Exports metadata configuration for SEO optimization and site information
- Provides essential structure wrapping all pages with:
  - Next-intl for internationalization
  - Vercel Analytics integration
  - Global providers for state management
  - Base navigation and footer components
  - Toast notifications
  - Custom fonts configuration
- Handles locale-based routing and message loading
- Implements structured data (JSON-LD) for SEO
- Configures base styling with Tailwind CSS and custom font classes

- Main page component for the root route ('/') of the application
- Wraps the InvoiceMain component in a main element with padding and container styling
- Imports and uses InvoiceMain component from the components directory
- Serves as the entry point for the invoice management interface
- Uses Next.js App Router format with locale support in the URL structure
- Exports a single default component for use as a page in Next.js routing

- Template viewer component that dynamically loads invoice templates based on URL parameter
- Exports a Next.js page component for viewing invoice templates at route `/[locale]/template/[id]`
- Uses dynamic imports to load specific invoice template components based on template number
- Accesses form data from parent context using React Hook Form
- Renders the selected template with sender, receiver, and details data from form values
- Other files can import this as a page component but it's primarily used by Next.js routing system
- Serves as a preview page for different invoice template designs

- API endpoint handler for exporting invoices using Next.js route handlers
- Exposes a single POST method that processes invoice export requests
- Delegates actual export functionality to the `exportInvoiceService`
- Acts as a bridge between client-side requests and server-side invoice export logic
- Can be accessed by frontend components through `/api/invoice/export` endpoint

- API route handler for generating invoice PDFs in a Next.js application
- Exposes a single POST endpoint that processes incoming invoice generation requests
- Delegates the actual PDF generation to the `generatePdfService` from the server-side invoice services
- Acts as a bridge between client-side requests and the server-side PDF generation logic

- Next.js API route handler for invoice email sending functionality
- Exposes POST endpoint at '/api/invoice/send'
- Utilizes `sendPdfToEmailService` from invoice services to handle email sending
- Returns HTTP 200 on success, HTTP 500 on failure
- Other files can make POST requests to this endpoint to trigger invoice PDF email sending

- Dev debug component used for development/testing purposes
- Exports a component that displays form state and debugging tools
- Utilizes React Hook Form context to access form state and reset functionality
- Provides quick navigation links to template pages
- Includes a button to fill form with test values from FORM_FILL_VALUES
- Styled with a distinctive red border to be easily identifiable in development
- No props required for implementation
- Must be used within a FormContext provider

Central index file that exports components for an invoice generation application
 Main categories of exports:
- Navigation components (navbar, footer)
- Invoice core components (main, form, actions)
- Form components and sections for invoice creation
- Reusable form fields and UI components
- Modal components for email, import/export, and signatures
- PDF invoice templates and email templates
 All components are imported from their respective folders and re-exported for use throughout the application
 Special development component (DevDebug) is included but marked as dev-only
 The file serves as a single source of truth for component imports across the application, following a barrel export pattern

- Client-side component that renders a card containing invoice-related action buttons and PDF preview
- Exports a single component `InvoiceActions` used in the invoice section
- Integrates with invoice context to handle loading states
- Key functionality:
  * Load invoice button with modal
  * Export invoice button with modal
  * New invoice button with alert confirmation
  * Generate PDF button
  * PDF viewer for preview
- Uses ShadCN UI components for styling and layout
- Requires invoice context to be available in parent component tree
- Fixed position card that sticks to top on scroll
- Takes up 45% width on XL screens

- A React component (`InvoiceForm`) that implements a multi-step wizard form for creating/editing invoices
- Uses React Hook Form for form management and validation
- Integrates with a translation context for internationalization
- Exports a default component that renders:
  * A card layout with title and invoice number badge
  * 5 wizard steps: Bill From/To, Invoice Details, Items, Payment Info, Summary
- Common import point for other components needing a complete invoice form interface
- Manages form state and watches invoice number changes using RHF's useWatch
- Designed to be used as client-side component ("use client" directive)
- Takes up 55% width on xl screens
- Uses ShadCN UI components for styling (Card, Badge)

- Main invoice component wrapper that handles form submission using React Hook Form
- Combines `InvoiceForm` and `InvoiceActions` components into a single form layout
- Uses `InvoiceContext` to handle form submission logic
- Exports `InvoiceMain` component for use in invoice-related pages
- Integrates with ShadCN Form component for styling and `InvoiceType` for type safety
- Primary purpose: Central form management and layout structure for invoice creation/editing

- Client-side component for displaying the final PDF invoice view and actions
- Exports a single component `FinalPdf` for use in invoice-related pages
- Depends on InvoiceContext for PDF operations (preview, download, print, save, email)
- Provides buttons for:
  * Returning to preview
  * Viewing PDF in new tab
  * Downloading PDF
  * Printing invoice
  * Saving invoice
  * Sending PDF via email
- Renders PDF preview in an iframe with fixed aspect ratio
- Uses ShadCN UI components and Lucide icons for styling

- React component that renders a live preview of an invoice
- Takes an InvoiceType data object as prop
- Uses DynamicInvoiceTemplate and Subheading components from app components
- Displays invoice preview inside a bordered container
- Primarily used to show real-time invoice updates when editing/creating invoices
- Exports a single component for use in other invoice-related views

- A client-side component that renders a PDF viewer for invoices
- Uses debounced form values from React Hook Form to update the preview
- Conditionally renders either a live preview or final PDF based on the invoicePdf state
- Exports a single component for use in invoice-related views
- Integrates with the InvoiceContext for PDF state management
- Main purpose: Provides real-time preview functionality for invoice generation
- Dependencies: use-debounce, react-hook-form, custom components (FinalPdf, LivePreview)

- React component for managing invoice charges and calculations
- Key functionality:
  * Handles discount, tax, and shipping switches and their amount types (percentage/fixed)
  * Displays subtotal and total amount with formatting
  * Toggles for including total amount in words
  * Uses React Hook Form for form management
  * Integrates with ChargesContext and TranslationContext
- Exports:
  * Default export: Charges component
  * Used in invoice form flows
  * Depends on ChargeInput component for amount inputs
  * Consumes shared UI components (Label, Switch)

- A form component for handling individual line items in an invoice
- Exports a SingleItem component used within invoice forms
- Key features:
  * Drag and drop functionality for reordering items
  * Auto-calculation of item totals based on quantity and unit price
  * Form fields: name, quantity, unit price, description
  * Support for moving items up/down and deletion
  * Integrated with React Hook Form for form management
  * Supports currency display and translations
Main usage:
- Used as a child component in invoice forms
- Handles single item entry and calculations
- Connected to parent form context for data management

- A React component (`TemplateSelector`) for selecting invoice PDF templates in a form
- Utilizes React Hook Form context to manage template selection state
- Exports a component that displays available invoice templates with preview images
- Uses ShadCN UI components for layout and styling
- Integrates with `InvoiceType` for form data typing
- Provides visual feedback for selected template with a checkmark icon
- Available templates are defined internally with IDs 1 and 2, linking to `InvoiceTemplate1` and `InvoiceTemplate2` components
- Template selection updates the form field "details.pdfTemplate" with the template ID

- A React form section component (`BillFromSection`) for handling sender/billing information in an invoice form
- Uses React Hook Form for form management with field array support for custom inputs
- Exports a section containing standard sender fields (name, address, etc.) and dynamic custom input fields
- Integrates with a translation system via `useTranslationContext`
- Main purpose: Collects and manages "Bill From" data for invoice generation
- Consumed by parent invoice form components that need sender information input functionality
- Notable features: Dynamic addition/removal of custom input fields and form field validation

- Client-side form section component for invoice billing details ("Bill To" section)
- Uses React Hook Form for form management (useFieldArray, useFormContext)
- Exports a form section containing input fields for receiver details (name, address, zip code, city, country, email, phone)
- Provides functionality to dynamically add/remove custom input fields
- Integrates with a translation system via useTranslationContext
- Rendered as part of a larger invoice form component
- Primarily used by the parent invoice form component for collecting billing information

- Client-side component that provides JSON invoice import functionality
- Exports a button component that triggers a file input dialog for JSON files
- Uses InvoiceContext to handle the import process and loading states
- Key dependencies: BaseButton, InvoiceContext, Lucide-react
- Component accepts a setOpen prop to control modal/dialog state
- Exposes functionality to import invoice data via JSON file format

- Client-side React component for handling invoice details form section
- Uses various form components (CurrencySelector, DatePicker, FormInput, etc.) to collect essential invoice information
- Integrates with a translation context for internationalization
- Exports a component that renders:
  * Invoice logo upload
  * Invoice number input
  * Issue date picker
  * Due date picker
  * Currency selector
  * Template selector
- Used as a section within a larger invoice form structure
- Main purpose is to gather and display basic invoice metadata in a structured form layout

- Component for rendering the summary section of an invoice form
- Integrates:
  * Signature handling with SignatureModal and SignatureContextProvider
  * Form fields for additional notes and payment terms
  * Charges calculation display
- Exports a client-side React component for use in invoice form flows
- Uses translation context for internationalization
- Primary purpose is to collect final invoice details and display total charges

- Component: Dynamic form section for managing invoice line items
- Key Features:
  * Drag-and-drop reordering of items using @dnd-kit
  * Form array management using React Hook Form
  * Add/remove/move item functionality
- Exports:
  * Default export of Items component for use in invoice form
- Dependencies:
  * Requires parent form context from React Hook Form
  * Uses translation context for internationalization
  * Relies on SingleItem component for individual item rendering
- Used By:
  * Main invoice form components
  * Expects to be wrapped in a FormProvider context

- Component responsible for rendering payment information section in invoice form
- Uses FormInput and Subheading components from app/components
- Integrates with TranslationContext for internationalization
- Exports a form section with three input fields: bank name, account name, and account number
- Input fields store data under the "details.paymentInformation" namespace
- Uses vertical layout pattern for form inputs with flex layout styles
- No direct business logic, purely presentational component
- Used as part of larger invoice form structure

- React component for wizard navigation controls in an invoice form context
- Uses `react-use-wizard` for step management
- Exports a component that provides "Next" and "Back" buttons for multi-step form navigation
- Integrates with translation system through TranslationContext
- Can be imported by other components needing wizard navigation controls
- Part of the invoice form wizard UI subsystem, providing navigation controls between steps

- A React component that manages and displays the progress bar for a multi-step invoice form wizard
- Exports a WizardProgress component that shows 5 steps: From/To, Invoice Details, Line Items, Payment Info, and Summary
- Uses react-hook-form for form validation status and react-use-wizard for wizard navigation
- Each step's button appearance changes based on validation state (valid/invalid) and active status
- Integrates with translation context for internationalized step labels
- Main functionality: navigation between wizard steps and visual indication of form completion status
- Used by parent invoice form components to display navigation and progress

- Client-side component that provides a single step container for a wizard form interface
- Uses `react-use-wizard` hook to handle wizard state and navigation
- Exports a reusable component that wraps step content with progress indicator and navigation controls
- Other files can use this as a wrapper for individual wizard form steps with consistent layout and controls
- Wrapper provides fixed minimum height, progress bar, and navigation buttons for all steps

- Simple footer component using `useClient` directive for client-side rendering
- Imports translation context for internationalization support
- Uses `AUTHOR_GITHUB` constant from variables
- Exports a basic footer layout component with author attribution and GitHub link
- Serves as a reusable footer component that can be imported by any page/component in the app

- React component that serves as the main navigation bar layout
- Exports a BaseNavbar component for use in other parts of the application
- Features: logo with link to home, language selector, theme switcher
- Shows debug component only in development environment
- Uses ShadCn Card component for styling and Next.js Image/Link components
- Positioned with z-index 99 to stay above other content

- A React component that manages the alert dialog for creating a new invoice
- Uses React Hook Form context to track form changes and prevent data loss
- Integrates with InvoiceContext to handle new invoice creation functionality
- Exports an alert dialog component that wraps child elements with confirmation logic when form has unsaved changes
- Key props:
  - children: React component (typically a button) that triggers the new invoice action
- Main dependencies:
  - shadcn/ui alert dialog components
  - react-hook-form
  - custom invoice context

- A React modal component for sending PDF documents via email
- Uses ShadCn Dialog components for the modal interface
- Exports a single component that requires:
  - sendPdfToMail: A callback function to handle email sending
  - children: React nodes for the trigger element
- Features:
  - Email validation
  - Loading states
  - Error handling
  - Automatic modal closing after successful send
- Primary use case: Invoice PDF delivery via email in the application

- A React modal component for exporting invoices in different formats
- Exports a single component `InvoiceExportModal` that accepts children as props
- Uses ShadCn Dialog components for modal UI
- Integrates with `InvoiceContext` to handle export functionality
- Provides export options for JSON, CSV, XML, and XLSX formats
- Requires `ExportTypes` enum from types and `useInvoiceContext` from contexts
- Can be triggered by wrapping any child component that will act as the modal opener

- Modal component for loading and managing saved invoices
- Exports a dialog/modal interface with a list of saved invoices and import functionality
- Uses ShadCn Dialog components for the modal UI
- Integrates with InvoiceContext to access saved invoices data
- Contains two main functional components:
  * SavedInvoicesList for displaying existing invoices
  * ImportJsonButton for importing invoice data
- Can be triggered by any children components passed to it
- Manages its own open/close state internally
- Primary purpose: Provides a reusable interface for loading saved invoices in other parts of the application

- A React component that displays a list of saved invoices with load/delete functionality
- Exports: Single default component `SavedInvoicesList` that receives a `setModalState` prop
- Dependencies: Uses React Hook Form context and Invoice context for state management
- Main functionality:
  * Displays saved invoices in a scrollable list
  * Allows loading invoice data back into the form
  * Provides option to load and generate PDF directly
  * Enables deletion of saved invoices
- Key consumed context:
  * `useInvoiceContext` for managing saved invoices
  * `useFormContext` for form state management
- Important note: Contains a TODO regarding removing 'any' type in updateFields function

- A modal component for managing digital signatures with three input methods: drawing, typing, and uploading
- Uses React Hook Form for form management and ShadCn UI components for the interface
- Exports a SignatureModal component that can be used in other files
- Integrates with SignatureContext and TranslationContext for state management
- Displays preview of existing signature and allows updating through different input methods
- Main interactions:
  - Handles signature data persistence across tab switches
  - Saves signature data to form context
  - Manages modal open/close state
  - Supports different signature formats (data URL, typed text)

- A React component for selecting signature colors in a modal dialog
- Exports a color selector component with clickable circular buttons
- Takes an array of colors, selected color, and click handler as props
- Uses BaseButton component for color options and Check icon to indicate selection
- Used by signature-related components to manage color selection for signatures

- A React component that renders a font selection dropdown for signature customization
- Uses ShadCn UI components for the select interface
- Takes array of signature fonts, selected font, and setter function as props
- Exports a single component for use in signature-related modals/forms
- Renders font names in their respective styles in the dropdown
- Integrated with custom SignatureFont type system for type safety
- Primary purpose is to allow users to choose different font styles for digital signatures

- Component that provides a drawing canvas for user signatures in a tab interface
- Exports a single component `DrawSignature` for use in signature-related modal interfaces
- Integrates with `SignatureContext` for managing signature state and actions
- Key features:
  * Canvas for drawing signatures with custom pen settings
  * Color selection functionality
  * Erase and save capabilities
  * Responsive canvas with max width of 600px
- Required props: `handleSaveSignature` callback function
- Uses ShadCN UI components for styling and layout
- Part of a larger signature modal system (indicated by TabsContent component)

- A React component for typed signature input within a tabbed interface
- Exports a single component 'TypeSignature' that handles typed signature creation
- Integrates with SignatureContext for state management
- Key features:
  - Text input for signature with customizable font
  - Font selector integration
  - Clear signature functionality
  - Save signature capability
- Dependencies:
  - Uses ShadCn UI components
  - Relies on SignatureContext for state management
  - Requires SignatureTabs type definition
- Used as a tab content in signature modal component

- A component for handling signature image uploads in a tabbed interface
- Exports a single component `UploadSignature` that manages the upload, display, and removal of signature images
- Integrates with `SignatureContext` for state management and signature handling functions
- Part of a larger signature management system, likely used in forms or document signing features
- Provides functionality to:
  * Upload image files
  * Display uploaded signature
  * Remove uploaded signature
  * Save signature changes
- Uses ShadCn UI components for styling and layout
- Required by parent components that need signature upload functionality

- A reusable React button component that extends ShadCn's Button component with additional functionality
- Exports a single component `BaseButton` that can be used across the application
- Key features:
  * Optional tooltip integration
  * Loading state with spinner
  * Customizable loading text
  * Type-safe props extending ButtonProps from ShadCn
  * Client-side component ("use client" directive)
- Dependencies: React, ShadCn UI components (Button, Tooltip), Lucide icons
- Used as a base button component throughout the application where consistent button behavior is needed

- Client-side language selector component built with Next.js and ShadCn UI components
- Uses next-intl for internationalization routing
- Exports a reusable dropdown component that allows users to switch between available languages
- Reads available languages from LOCALES constant and current locale from URL params
- Displays a BETA badge and handles language switching through next-intl router
- Primarily used in layout/header components for global language selection

- A reusable React component that renders subheadings (h4) with consistent styling
- Exports a single function component that accepts children as props
- Applies standardized text styling: extra-large size (text-xl) and semi-bold font weight
- Located in reusables folder indicating it's meant for repeated use across the application
- Primary purpose is to maintain heading hierarchy and consistent typography in the UI

- Client-side component that provides a theme switching button
- Utilizes next-themes for theme management
- Exports a single button component that toggles between light/dark themes
- Uses animated Sun/Moon icons from lucide-react for visual feedback
- Can be imported and used anywhere in the app where theme switching is needed
- Depends on BaseButton component from local components library
- Accessibility features included through sr-only text

- A reusable form component for handling charge/fee inputs in a React application
- Exports a `ChargeInput` component that toggles between percentage and fixed amount inputs
- Uses React Hook Form (RHF) for form management
- Integrates with ShadCN UI components for styling
- Provides input validation with min/max constraints (0-1000000)
- Key features:
  - Toggle button to switch between percentage/fixed amount
  - Shows either % or currency symbol based on input type
  - Form field integration with parent form context
  - Custom label and name prop support
  - Currency display option

- A React form component that renders a currency selection dropdown using ShadCn UI components
- Integrates with React Hook Form for form state management
- Uses a custom `useCurrencies` hook to fetch available currencies
- Exports a reusable CurrencySelector component that accepts name, label, and placeholder props
- Main use: Form fields that require currency selection in the application
- Key dependencies: @shadcn/ui, react-hook-form
- Component is client-side rendered ("use client" directive)
- Accessible by other components for forms requiring currency input/selection

- A reusable React form field component for date picking functionality
- Uses React Hook Form for form management and ShadCN UI components
- Exports a DatePickerFormField component that can be used in any form within the application
- Features:
  - Calendar popup interface for date selection
  - Date range limitation (1900-01-01 to current year + 30)
  - Formatting of selected dates using DATE_OPTIONS
  - Form field integration with validation support
- Props interface accepts:
  - name: field name for form context
  - label: optional display label for the field

- A reusable form component that renders a key-value pair input field with a delete button
- Exports a single functional component `FormCustomInput` that takes index, location, and removeField props
- Designed for dynamic form fields where users can input custom key-value pairs
- Uses BaseButton and FormInput from internal components
- Each field consists of a name input (key), value input, and delete button
- Location prop is used to construct unique field names for form handling
- Primarily used in forms that need customizable field collections or metadata input

- Client-side form component for handling file/image uploads using React Hook Form
- Provides a reusable file input field that converts uploaded images to base64 strings
- Exports a single component `FormFile` that can be used in other forms
- Key features:
  * Image preview functionality
  * Base64 conversion for form submission
  * Remove image capability
  * Integrates with React Hook Form for form state management
- Required props: name (form field name)
- Optional props: label, placeholder
- Used for image upload interfaces like logo uploads in forms

- Reusable form input component that integrates React Hook Form with ShadCN UI components
- Exports a single component 'FormInput' that can be used in other form components
- Key features:
  * Supports both vertical and horizontal layout modes
  * Integrates with React Hook Form context
  * Uses ShadCN Input component with form validation
  * Customizable with label, helper text, and placeholder
  * Compatible with standard HTML input props
- Required in parent: Must be used within a React Hook Form FormProvider context

- Custom React textarea component integrating React Hook Form and ShadCn UI components
- Exports reusable form textarea field with label, helper text, and validation support
- Accepts standard textarea props plus custom form-specific props (name, label, labelHelper)
- Uses useFormContext() hook from React Hook Form for form state management
- Commonly used by other files for form text area input handling within the application

- Email template component for sending PDF invoice confirmations
- Used with react-email/components library and Tailwind CSS styling
- Accepts invoiceNumber as prop to personalize the email
- Defines a structured HTML email layout with logo, invoice number reference, and standard email content
- Main component `SendPdfEmail` is exported for use in email sending functionality elsewhere in the application
- Dependent on BASE_URL from lib/variables for logo image path
- Used as template file for generating transactional emails when invoices are ready for download

- A React component that dynamically loads different invoice PDF templates based on a template number
- Exports a single component `DynamicInvoiceTemplate` which accepts `InvoiceType` props
- Uses Next.js dynamic imports to load specific invoice template files lazily
- Shows a skeleton loading state while template is being loaded
- Templates must follow naming convention: `InvoiceTemplate{number}.tsx`
- Used as a template switcher/loader for different invoice PDF layouts
- Disables server-side rendering (SSR) for the dynamic templates

- Layout component for rendering PDF invoices with consistent styling
- Accepts InvoiceType data object and child components as props
- Dynamically loads fonts including a custom signature font if specified
- Exports a reusable layout wrapper that other invoice-related components can use
- Sets up basic page structure with padding, background, and minimum height
- Component is used in PDF generation process and provides consistent styling for invoice documents

- React component defining the first invoice template layout and design (InvoiceTemplate1)
- Uses InvoiceLayout component as a wrapper
- Accepts InvoiceType as props containing sender, receiver, and details information
- Key features exported for use:
  * Renders invoice header with logo and company details
  * Shows billing information and dates
  * Displays itemized list of products/services
  * Calculates and shows totals, taxes, discounts
  * Includes payment terms and bank details
  * Optional signature display (image or text)
- Used by other components needing to render this specific invoice template style
- Relies on helper functions: formatNumberWithCommas, isDataUrl
- Uses global DATE_OPTIONS constant for date formatting

- This file exports a React component `InvoiceTemplate2` that renders a specific invoice template design
- It is a presentational component that takes an `InvoiceType` data object containing sender, receiver, and invoice details
- Key features:
  - Uses InvoiceLayout as a wrapper component
  - Displays invoice header with logo and company details
  - Shows itemized list of products/services
  - Calculates and displays subtotals, taxes, discounts
  - Includes payment information and signature section
- Used by other files that need to generate invoices with this specific template design
- Depends on helper functions for number formatting and data URL validation
- Utilizes predefined date formatting options from variables

- Root layout component for Next.js application structure
- Acts as a minimal pass-through layout without additional styling or wrapping
- Required due to existence of root-level `not-found.tsx` page
- Imports global CSS styles for application-wide styling
- Exports a simple layout component that renders its children directly
- Used by Next.js framework to wrap all pages and provide base structure
- Typescript implementation with ReactNode typing for children prop

This is a Next.js 404 error page component that handles routes without locale associations
 Exports a single default function `NotFound` that renders Next.js default 404 error page
 Uses the 'use client' directive indicating it's a client-side component
 Implements minimal HTML structure with English language attribute
 Utilizes Next.js built-in Error component with 404 status code
 Serves as a fallback for routes not matched by the middleware

- Root page component that automatically redirects visitors to the English language route ("/en")
- Used as an entry point for the application's static build
- Exports a single default function `RootPage` that performs the redirection
- Simple routing mechanism utilizing Next.js' built-in `redirect` function
- No direct exports of variables or additional functions for other files to use

- A client-side React component that provides an accessible alert dialog UI using Radix UI primitives
- Exports 11 styled components that can be imported and composed to create alert dialogs:
  - Core: AlertDialog (root), AlertDialogTrigger, AlertDialogPortal
  - Layout: AlertDialogOverlay, AlertDialogContent, AlertDialogHeader, AlertDialogFooter
  - Content: AlertDialogTitle, AlertDialogDescription
  - Actions: AlertDialogAction, AlertDialogCancel
- Includes default styling via Tailwind CSS classes and animations for dialog transitions
- Depends on @radix-ui/react-alert-dialog for base components and local button/utils for styling
- Used for displaying important messages that require user acknowledgment or confirmation

- A React component that exports an aspect ratio container utility from Radix UI
- Provides a wrapper to maintain consistent width/height ratios for child elements
- Simply re-exports the Root component from @radix-ui/react-aspect-ratio
- Other files can import {AspectRatio} to create responsive containers with fixed aspect ratios
- Client-side component (marked with "use client" directive)

- A React component that provides a customizable badge/tag UI element
- Exports: `Badge` component and `badgeVariants` styling configuration
- Supports 4 visual variants: default, secondary, destructive, and outline
- Uses class-variance-authority (cva) for style variants management
- Can be composed with standard HTML div attributes and custom className props
- Primary use case: displaying status indicators, labels, or tags in the UI
- Dependencies: React, class-variance-authority, and internal utils for class name merging

- Reusable Button component for React applications using TailwindCSS and class-variance-authority
- Exports:
  - `Button`: Main component with support for variants, sizes, and child components
  - `buttonVariants`: Style configuration object for standalone use
- Variants: default, destructive, outline, secondary, ghost, link
- Sizes: default, sm, lg, icon
- Integrates with Radix UI's Slot primitive for component polymorphism
- All standard button HTML attributes supported through ButtonProps interface
- Uses class merging utility (cn) for className handling

- A customized Calendar component wrapper around `react-day-picker` with styled UI elements
- Exports a single `Calendar` component with associated `CalendarProps` type
- Integrates with custom UI components (Select, ScrollArea, Button) for enhanced functionality
- Features styled dropdowns for month/year selection and navigation buttons
- Can be imported and used by other components requiring date-picking functionality with a consistent UI theme

- A React component library that exports customizable card-related UI components
- Exports 6 components: Card, CardHeader, CardFooter, CardTitle, CardDescription, CardContent
- Each component is a styled div/heading/paragraph using Tailwind CSS classes
- Uses forwardRef for proper ref handling in React
- Components have default styling but accept className prop for customization
- Components rely on utils.cn function for class name merging
- Follows a consistent structure with header, content, footer sections
- Used for creating card-based layouts in other parts of the application

- A React client component that exports a customized Dialog implementation using Radix UI's Dialog primitives
- Provides styled and accessible modal dialog components with animations and responsive design
- Exports main components for use in other files:
  * Dialog (root container)
  * DialogPortal (portal container)
  * DialogOverlay (backdrop/overlay)
  * DialogTrigger (button to open dialog)
  * DialogContent (main content wrapper)
  * DialogHeader (styled header section)
  * DialogFooter (styled footer section)
  * DialogTitle (styled title component)
  * DialogDescription (styled description text)
- Uses tailwind classes for styling and animations
- Integrates with project's design system through cn utility for class merging

- A form component library built with React that integrates React Hook Form and Radix UI primitives
- Exports reusable form components and hooks:
  - Form: Base form provider wrapper
  - FormField: Field controller with context
  - FormItem: Container for form elements
  - FormLabel: Form label with error states
  - FormControl: Slot-based form control wrapper
  - FormDescription: Helper text component
  - FormMessage: Error message display
  - useFormField: Custom hook for field state management
- Provides styled and accessible form elements with built-in error handling and validation support
- Designed to be used by other components/pages needing form functionality with consistent styling and behavior

- A reusable React Input component with styling using Tailwind CSS
- Exports `Input` component and `InputProps` interface
- Extends native HTML input attributes
- Uses React.forwardRef for ref forwarding
- Styling includes border, rounded corners, focus states, and disabled states
- Other files can import and use this styled input component
- Integrates with cn utility for className merging
- Designed as part of a UI component library system

- UI component that provides a styled form label element using Radix UI's Label primitive
- Exports a single `Label` component that can be used in other files for form accessibility
- Uses class-variance-authority for style variants and utilities for class name merging
- Implements peer styling for disabled states with cursor and opacity modifications
- Component is client-side rendered (marked with "use client" directive)
- Main use case is for creating accessible form labels that match the design system

- A React component library file that exports styled navigation menu components using Radix UI primitives
- Main exports:
  - `NavigationMenu`: Root container component
  - `NavigationMenuList`: Container for menu items
  - `NavigationMenuItem`: Individual menu item
  - `NavigationMenuTrigger`: Clickable trigger with dropdown arrow
  - `NavigationMenuContent`: Dropdown content container
  - `NavigationMenuLink`: Navigation link component
  - `NavigationMenuIndicator`: Visual indicator for active items
  - `NavigationMenuViewport`: Viewport for dropdown content
  - `navigationMenuTriggerStyle`: Reusable styling function for triggers
- Dependencies:
  - @radix-ui/react-navigation-menu
  - class-variance-authority
  - lucide-react (for ChevronDown icon)
- Uses utility function `cn` from "@/lib/utils" for class name handling
- Provides fully styled and accessible navigation menu components with animations and responsive behavior

- React component that exports a customized Popover UI element based on Radix UI's Popover primitive
- Exports three components: `Popover` (root), `PopoverTrigger`, and `PopoverContent`
- PopoverContent is styled with animations, shadows, and positioning using Tailwind CSS
- Dependent on @radix-ui/react-popover library and local utils for className merging
- Used by other components to create floating content panels that appear when triggered

- React component that exports a customizable scrollable area with a custom scrollbar using Radix UI primitives
- Exports two components: `ScrollArea` (main wrapper) and `ScrollBar` (customizable scrollbar)
- Accepts standard React props and className for styling customization
- Component uses client-side rendering ("use client")
- Supports both vertical and horizontal scrolling orientations
- Can be imported and used by other components to create scrollable content areas with styled scrollbars
- Integrates with project's utility function `cn` for className merging

- Custom styled select component built on top of @radix-ui/react-select
- Exports reusable select components: Select (root), SelectGroup, SelectValue, SelectTrigger (button), SelectContent (dropdown), SelectLabel, SelectItem, and SelectSeparator
- Uses Tailwind CSS for styling through cn utility function
- Components are accessible and customizable through className props
- Can be used client-side only ("use client" directive)
- Dependencies: React, @radix-ui/react-select, lucide-react (for icons), and local utils for className merging

- A React component called `Skeleton` that creates loading placeholder animations
- Exports a single component used to display loading states throughout the application
- Utilizes the `cn` utility for class name merging and tailwind styling
- Implements pulse animation and rounded edges via Tailwind CSS classes
- Can be imported by other files to create loading state placeholders with customizable styles through className prop
- Most commonly used in conjunction with conditional rendering while data is being fetched

- A custom Switch component built on top of Radix UI's Switch primitive
- Exports a single `Switch` component that can be used as a toggle/switch input
- Styled using Tailwind CSS with support for focus states, hover, and disabled states
- Integrates with the application's theme system through `cn` utility
- Accessible by default due to Radix UI primitives
- Can be imported and used in other React components that need toggle functionality

- A React component library that exports reusable styled table components
- Uses Tailwind CSS for styling through the `cn` utility function
- Exports 8 components: Table, TableHeader, TableBody, TableFooter, TableHead, TableRow, TableCell, TableCaption
- All components are forward ref components that extend HTML table element attributes
- Main features:
  - Responsive table with overflow handling
  - Hover and selected states for rows
  - Consistent styling and spacing
  - Supports custom className props for style overrides
- Used by other components that need to display tabular data with consistent styling

- A React client-side component that provides a customized tab interface using Radix UI's tab primitives
- Exports 4 components: `Tabs` (root), `TabsList` (container), `TabsTrigger` (tab button), and `TabsContent` (content panel)
- Components use the `cn` utility for className merging and include default styling with support for custom classes
- Built with TypeScript and includes proper type definitions through React.forwardRef
- Styling includes focus states, transitions, and active states with support for muted/foreground theming
- Used by other files to create tabbed interfaces with consistent styling and accessibility features

- A React component for a styled textarea element using shadcn/ui design system
- Exports a `Textarea` component and its props interface (`TextareaProps`)
- Extends native HTML textarea attributes through React's TextareaHTMLAttributes
- Uses utility function `cn` from "@/lib/utils" for class name merging
- Provides default styling including dimensions, border, colors, and focus states
- Can be customized through className prop while maintaining base styles
- Implements React.forwardRef for ref forwarding capabilities

- A custom toast component built on top of Radix UI's toast primitives (@radix-ui/react-toast)
- Exports a complete toast system with styled components: Provider, Viewport, Toast, Title, Description, Close, and Action
- Includes two variant styles: default and destructive, managed through class-variance-authority (cva)
- Main exports can be used by other files to create notification toasts with consistent styling and behavior
- Features responsive design, animations, and swipe interactions for toast dismissal
- Integrates with the application's theme through utility classes and custom styling hooks (cn utility)
- Other files can import individual components or types (ToastProps, ToastActionElement) to build custom toast notifications

- A React component `Toaster` that provides a toast notification system for the application
- Uses shadcn/ui toast components for rendering notifications
- Exports a single component `Toaster` that can be imported and used by other files
- Manages toast notifications through the `useToast` hook
- Each toast can display a title, description, custom actions, and a close button
- Client-side component as indicated by "use client" directive
- Dependent on the `components/ui/toast` and `components/ui/use-toast` modules

- UI component for creating tooltips using Radix UI's TooltipPrimitive
- Exports four main components: Tooltip (root), TooltipTrigger, TooltipContent, and TooltipProvider
- TooltipContent includes default styling with animations, positioning, and theme-aware colors
- Uses client-side rendering ("use client")
- Utilizes utility function 'cn' for class name merging
- Can be imported by other components to add tooltip functionality with consistent styling

- Custom React toast management hook inspired by react-hot-toast
- Exports:
  - `useToast` hook: Manages toast state and provides toast controls
  - `toast` function: Creates and manages individual toasts
  - `reducer` function: Handles toast state updates
- Key features:
  - Limited to 1 toast at a time (TOAST_LIMIT = 1)
  - Supports toast creation, updating, dismissal, and removal
  - Auto-removes toasts after delay (TOAST_REMOVE_DELAY)
  - Maintains global toast state using listeners pattern
  - Integrates with a companion toast UI component (imported from "@/components/ui/toast")

- React Context provider for managing invoice charges, calculations, and total amounts
- Exports:
  * ChargesContext: Context object for charge-related states
  * useChargesContext: Custom hook to access the charges context
  * ChargesContextProvider: Provider component that handles charge calculations
- Manages states for:
  * Discount, tax, and shipping charges (amount/percentage)
  * Toggle switches for enabling/disabling charges
  * Currency and total amount calculations
  * Total amount in words functionality
- Uses React Hook Form for form management
- Automatically calculates totals when charge values change
- Other components can consume this context to access invoice charge states and calculations

- Context provider for invoice-related functionality in a React/Next.js application
- Main exports:
  - InvoiceContext: Context object for invoice state
  - useInvoiceContext: Custom hook to access invoice context
  - InvoiceContextProvider: Provider component that manages invoice state
- Key features exposed to other files:
  - PDF generation, preview, download, and printing
  - Invoice saving and loading from localStorage
  - Email functionality for sending invoices
  - Import/Export capabilities for invoice data
  - Form submission handling
  - PDF blob management and loading states
- Dependencies:
  - React Hook Form for form management
  - Next.js navigation
  - Custom toast notifications
  - Invoice service for export functionality
- State management for:
  - PDF blob data
  - Loading states
  - Saved invoices in localStorage
  - Form data through React Hook Form

- Main provider component wrapper for the application that combines multiple context providers
- Integrates React Hook Form with Zod validation for invoice data management
- Wraps the application with:
  * Theme management (light/dark/system)
  * Translation support
  * Form context with invoice schema validation
  * Invoice context
  * Charges context
- Exports a single Provider component that should wrap the root of the application
- Uses default form values from FORM_DEFAULT_VALUES constant

- Context provider for managing digital signatures in a React application
- Exports:
  - SignatureContext: Context object for signature state
  - useSignatureContext: Custom hook to access signature context
  - SignatureContextProvider: Provider component that manages signature state
Key functionalities exposed to other files:
- Drawing signature management (canvas, colors, clear functions)
- Typed signature handling (text input, fonts, sizing)
- Uploaded signature processing (file upload, image conversion)
- Integration with react-hook-form for form management
- Base64 signature data storage and manipulation
Used by components that need to handle signature creation, editing, or display in the application.

A client-side component that wraps the Next.js application with theme functionality using next-themes library
 Exports a single `ThemeProvider` component that other components can use to enable theme switching capabilities
 Allows child components to access and manipulate theme settings through Next.js theme context
 Simply passes through props to the underlying NextThemesProvider component

- A React context provider for handling translations using next-intl
- Exports:
  - TranslationContext: Context object for translations
  - useTranslation & useTranslationContext: Hook to access translations
  - TranslationProvider: Component wrapper that provides translation context
- Used in components that need access to translation functionality through a simple _t() function
- Centralizes translation management and provides consistent access across the application

A React custom hook that fetches and manages a list of currencies from an external API
 Exports two states: `currencies` (array of currency objects with code/name) and `currenciesLoading` (boolean loading state)
 Automatically fetches currencies on component mount
 Dependencies: Requires CURRENCIES_API from "@/lib/variables" and CurrencyType from "@/types"
 Primary use case: Components needing access to a list of available currencies and their loading state

* Custom hook for managing toast notifications using ShadCn's toast component
* Exports pre-configured toast notifications for invoice-related actions:
  - New invoice creation
  - PDF generation
  - Invoice saving
  - Invoice modification
  - PDF email sending
  - Error handling for PDF sending
  - Error handling for invoice imports
* Used by components/pages that need to display toast notifications for invoice operations
* Depends on ShadCn UI components (@/components/ui/toast and @/components/ui/use-toast)
